 the next seven decades but by  it was surpassed in turn by both petroleum and natural gas in  coal consumption was the highest it has ever been with coal mostly being used to generate electricity natural gas which is cleanerburning and more easily transportable has replaced coal as the preferred source of heating in homes businesses and industrial furnaces although total energy use increased by approximately a factor of  between  and  energy use per capita increased only by a factor of four as of  united states per capita energy use had declined to  kilograms of oilequivalent  less than  and through  most recent available is at levels not seen since s usage levels at the beginning of the th century petroleum was a minor resource used to manufacture lubricants and fuel for kerosene and oil lamps one hundred years later it had become the preeminent energy source for the us and the rest of the world this rise closely paralleled the emergence of the automobile as a major force in american culture and the economy while petroleum is also used as a source for plastics and other chemicals and powers various industrial processes today twothirds of oil consumption in the us is in the form of its derived transportation fuels oils unique qualities for transportation fuels in terms of energy content cost of production and speed of refueling all contributed to it being used over other fuels in june  the american energy innovation council a group which includes bill gates founder of microsoft jeffrey r immelt chief executive of general electric and john doerr has urged the government to more than triple spending on energy research and development to  billion a year mr gates endorsed the administrations goal of reducing greenhouse gas emissions by  percent by  but said that was not possible with todays technology or politicism he said that the only way to find such disruptive new technology was to pour large sums of money at the problem the group notes that the federal government spends less than  billion a year on energy research and development not counting onetime stimulus projects about  billion is spent annually on health research and more than  billion on military r d they advocate a jump in spending on basic energy research us co emissions have dropped about  per year through greater efficiency and a sluggish economy since  current consumptionedit main article energy supply energy in the united states capita prim energy production import electricity coemission million twh twh twh twh mt                                           r              change        mtoe   twh prim energy includes energy losses that are  for nuclear power r  co calculation criteria changed numbers updated primary energy use in the united states was  twh or about  kwh per person in  primary energy use was  twh less in the us than in china in  same year the share of energy import in the us was  of the primary energy use the energy import declined ca  and the annual co emissions ca  in  compared to  us energy flow   a quad is  btu or  ×  joules note the breakdown of useful and waste energy in each sector dark vs light grey due to the nature of heat engines which cannot convert all thermal energy into useful work and consequently lose a portion of their heat to the environment us primary energy consumption by source and sector  from the us energy information administration department of energy consumption by sectoredit the us department of energy tracks national energy consumption in four broad sectors industrial transportation residential and commercial the industrial sector has long been the countrys largest energy user currently representing about  of the total next in importance is the transportation sector followed by the residential and commercial sectors sector summary sector name description major uses industrial facilities and equipment used for producing and processing goods  chemical production  petroleum refining  metal smeltingrefining transportation v