rs later it had become the preeminent energy source for the us and the rest of the world this rise closely paralleled the emergence of the automobile as a major force in american culture and the economy while petroleum is also used as a source for plastics and other chemicals and powers various industrial processes today twothirds of oil consumption in the us is in the form of its derived transportation fuels oils unique qualities for transportation fuels in terms of energy content cost of production and speed of refueling all contributed to it being used over other fuels in june  the american energy innovation council a group which includes bill gates founder of microsoft jeffrey r immelt chief executive of general electric and john doerr has urged the government to more than triple spending on energy research and development to  billion a year mr gates endorsed the administrations goal of reducing greenhouse gas emissions by  percent by  but said that was not possible with todays technology or politicism he said that the only way to find such disruptive new technology was to pour large sums of money at the problem the group notes that the federal government spends less than  billion a year on energy research and development not counting onetime stimulus projects about  billion is spent annually on health research and more than  billion on military r d they advocate a jump in spending on basic energy research us co emissions have dropped about  per year through greater efficiency and a sluggish economy since  current consumptionedit main article energy supply energy in the united states capita prim energy production import electricity coemission million twh twh twh twh mt                                           r              change        mtoe   twh prim energy includes energy losses that are  for nuclear power r  co calculation criteria changed numbers updated primary energy use in the united states was  twh or about  kwh per person in  primary energy use was  